data.name: Label6.Text
data.value:
This Wizard will guide you trough the setup for using this app.
The following things are nesseary for configuring Yealink Dialer.
Phone IP Sip account username Sip server IP WebUI Username WebUI Password
Click [Next] to proceed to the next step.

data.name: Label7.Text
data.value:
Before the app can communicate with the phone, you need to setup the Action URI Allow IP List.
1. Login to your phones web interface.
2. The image on the right shows you where to find the correct page.
3. Input your / all computer IP's from which you might want to make API requests from.
You can specify multiple IP's or use wildcards (*) to specify IP / Subnet ranges.
A wildcard is used in the example thus allowing the IP range from 192.168.1.1 up until 192.168.1.255 to make requests to the phone.
4. Make sure you click [Confirm] Then proceed onto the next step.

data.name: Label1.Text
data.value:
Input your phones IP address here. By default no port is needed, but can be additionally specified if nesseary. You can also specify if you want to use SSL and to ignore the certificate check. (Most phones will need this)
Example: 192.168.1.100

data.name: Label2.Text
data.value:
Here you can specify the SIP account to use for outgoing calls trough this app and the SIP Servers IP address. (Optional) The format for this is: SIPUSERNAME@SIPSERVERIP
Example: JOHNDOE@192.168.1.1

data.name: Label10.Text
data.value:
If you confingured everything right, we should now be able to test the phone connection.
The first time you send a request to your phone, or if certain phone settings have been updated. The phones screen will show you a information text, asking you to confirm the remote connection.
Hit the test button, and watch your phone screen. If you see the info text Yealink Dialer successfully send the request to your phone. Confirm the message so the phone accepts it's connection.
Hitting test again should now initiate a test call to a invalid number.
If successfull, you can proceed to the next page. Should you not have received any confirmation message and the phone does nothing. Please go back 1 page and check your data again.

data.name: Label14.Text
data.value:
Password reveal lockout will cause the password field to be locked after load. If saved with this checked, unchecking will force clear the password field.
Clearing only happens once, this prevents accidental nuking during setup. This is also reflected by the striked out icon not reappearing until saving again. It will nuke again the next time, if it was saved with this on again.
